nodes.bodyText:
I think these two parameters are sufficient for increasing the default message size. By default it is 1MB, you may want to increase it to 10MB.
kafkaConfig.putIfAbsent(ProducerConfig.COMPRESSION_TYPE_CONFIG, "snappy");
kafkaConfig.putIfAbsent(ProducerConfig.MAX_REQUEST_SIZE_CONFIG, 1000000);
Also we should allow the config to be added from osgi configuration just like here
The loaded config should override anything that we set here.  So we can totally skip these defaults and allow user to add them.

